RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 79. Maiden Special Weight Purse 67000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: POINT AND SHOOT broke a hair slow then took back to avoid trouble between rivals, trailed two wide early, trailed three wide into the far turn, moved further out and came four wide into the stretch, rallied to the front past the eighth pole and drew away. STAY IN LINE set the pace on the inside under pressure, maintained command into the final furlong, then relinquished the lead to POINT AND SHOOT and stayed on to secure second. SMOOVE AS SILK broke a bit slow on the outside, tracked the pace outside a rival early, went between foes into the second bend, got boxed in and had to steady losing positions, tipped three wide into the lane and got up for the show. YVETT'S SURPRISE broke a step slow, reserved early and moved into the two path, steered out while moving into range and advancing up the backstretch, rounded that bend four then three wide, could not summon the needed late kick and was edged for the show. TURQUOISE BIKINI broke inward and was quickly corrected, pulled around the first turn then prompted the pace outside the leader, kept the pressure on to upper stretch, then weakened in the furlong grounds. CEE MINUS sat off the pace from inside, lacked room behind a rival near the five-sixteenths pole, cut the corner into the lane, found traffic briefly again in upper stretch, tipped out and could not rally. LOVE OUR FAMILY stalked along the inside, saved ground to the stretch, lacked room from upper to midstretch, then failed to respond once gaining a clear path. PALACSINTA chased in range three deep early, rounded the far turn three then two wide and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Yvett's Surprise
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, reserved, 2wide, 4-3wide, lost 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Stay in Line
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace inside, no match late

ENTRY.NAME: Cee Minus
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, lacked room 5/16, traffic upper, no rally

ENTRY.OWNER: Howard and Janet Siegel Racing LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, lacked room upper-midstretch, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Turquoise Bikini
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, pulled, pressed outside, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Palacsinta
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 3deep, 2wide, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Smoove as Silk
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, tracked 2wide, boxed in/steadied 2nd, gained 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 26000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, For Each $1,750 To $12,500 1 lb.

CLAIM.OWNER: Metanoia Racing and Peachy Dandy Racing Stables

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TROJAN WAY sped clear and steered to the inside, pressured from outside up the backstretch, headed by SWEET HEIDELBERG on the far turn, lost the lead with a quarter mile remaining, fought back from inside through the lane, regained command in the final sixteenth and inched ahead. SWEET HEIDELBERG was a bit fractious in the gate, stalked two wide early then went up to apply pressure up the backstretch, headed TROJAN WAY on the far turn, took at the quarter pole, carried a short lead into the final furlong but got outfinished in the final sixteenth. LUCY L was rank chasing along the rail on the first turn, went two then three wide on the second bend, failed to make any headway on the top pair but was well clear of the next rival. GLORY OF CHROME tracked three wide early then dropped back and raced outside a rival at the back, continued three wide through the second bend and could not rally. DISTORTED QUEEN lost her footing in the hind-quarters at the start and trailed into the first turn, pulled while trying to be reserved around the bend, saved ground at the back and weakened in the drive.

ENTRY.COMMENT: rank early, chased inside, 2-3wide, clear 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 3 6 1/2F Turf CR: 92. Claiming Purse 43000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 17 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000, For Each $2,000 To $28,000 2 lbs. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GALLOVIE (GB) dueled for the lead from inside early then inched ahead past the quarter pole, cleared with a quarter mile left to run, drew off when roused in upper stretch and coasted in hand late. MONGOLIAN PANTHER trailed three wide into the stretch, angled out widest in the lane and summoned a mild rally to best the rest. INVINCIBELLA (GB) stalked the speed from inside into the turn, lost some ground around the bend and was put to right-handed urging, angled out in upper stretch and gained the show. VEGAN bumped leaving the gate, stalked off the rail then between foes into the turn, moved out and came three wide into the stretch and lacked a rally. DEL MAR DRAMA bumped with VEGAN at the start, showed early speed and dueled outside GALLOVIE (GB) then pressed up the backstretch, lost touch with the leader nearing the quarter pole and weakened in the drive. KITTEN'S KID broke out and was quickly corrected, raced up close outside the leaders, chased three deep then two wide into the lane and faded. ORIGINALLY HAND-TIMED, TIMES CHANGED UPON REVIEW.

ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, 3wide into str, angled widest str, mild rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 78. Maiden Claiming Purse 34000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000, For Each $2,500 To $35,000 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ TOK bobbled leaving the gate but still came away at the front, was closest in pursuit in the two path early, went up to vie between and took over on the backstretch, dueled inside ICE STORM through the far turn holding a short advantage, shook free at the top of the stretch and drew off under right handed urging and steady handling in deep stretch. ICE STORM chased between rivals and brushed three deep into the first turn then got boxed in around the bend, went up to challenge three deep in the middle stages, dueled outside TIZ TOK around the far turn, could not kick on with that rival in upper stretch but stayed on to prove second best. STREET MOGUL got brushed while four deep into the first turn, stalked the top trio outside a rival in the middle stages, rounded the far turn in the three path and bested the others. GLENDALE trailed four wide early, continued in the four path on the second bend and kept on to earn a minor award while never threatening. EXTRA INNINGS sped to the front from inside, challenged by an outside pair on the backstretch, lost command and vied to the far turn, lost ground to the leaders while under heavy urging around that bend and gave way. TAPIT DOWN broke a step slow then was coaxed between to a forward position in the two path, took a bad step early on the far turn and had little left for the drive. VINCE'S CORNER chased on the inside then dropped back to last in the middle stages, saved ground at the back into the lane and failed to menace. ANTICIPATED had to steady when losing his path early, sat off the pace outside a rival, got blocked behind rival at the five-sixteenths pole, came three wide into the stretch and made no impact.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 5 6F Turf CR: 102. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 72000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Clai ming, Or Starter Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $16,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts Preferred)(Horses Entered For The Allowance Are Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FORGIVING SPIRIT broke a step slow, went up to take a stalking position outside a rival, flanked the lead into the turn, chased two wide around the bend, challenged under left handed urging with a furlong remaining, took a narrow lead at the sixteenth pole, drifted in and brushed the runner-up late and prevailed. IN VRONSKY STYLE sprinted clear early and moved inside, showed the way to the stretch, challenged at the eighth pole, fought back into deep stretch, got brushed by FORGIVING SPIRIT and was yielded grudgingly. OUBABE sat off the pace, went inside a pair of rivals into the turn, saved ground to the stretch, then tipped out and whittled gap on the top pair late. JOE DON LOONEY sat off the pace while widest early, spun four wide into the lane and earned a minor award while failing to threaten. MINISTER SHANE tracked off the rail then three deep into the turn, coaxed along in the three path to the stretch and could not rally. DIVINE RASCAL took an awkward step crossing over the dirt, chased four wide into the turn, got shuffled between and steered down to the inside and lacked further response. WHO'S CANDY broke a step slow, drifted out early, got bumped by outer rival then took hold near near the nine-sixteenths pole, coaxed along past the half-mile pole, chased two wide on the turn and weakened. HESA BLUE GRASS was off slow in the beginning and never got involved.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 97. Claiming Purse 26000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.

CLAIM.OWNER: Purple Rein Racing O'Neill Dennis and O'Neill Doug F

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOKER BOY settled early, went between rivals in the two path on the turn, moved out in the lane, closed in under right handed urging and overhauled the runner-up late. SAWASDEE brushed inner rival early, raced up close three deep then outside the leader, dueled on the turn and took over at the quarter pole, shook free in upper stretch but got run down late. SINGLE ME OUT raced in range off the rail, spun three wide into the lane, continued within striking distance but lacked a late bid and held the show. SONIC BREES got blocked behind a rival early, traveled near the back up the backstretch, steadied at the seven-sixteenths pole, went between foes then three wide into the lane and kept on for a minor award. BUTKUS had to steady early then angled out racing at the back, was blocked on the turn in the three path, angled out and came six wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. SANTA CRUISER got brushed from outside early, chased four then five wide on the turn and lacked a rally. SAVILE ROW was forced to steady early, tracked three then four wide and failed to respond when called upon. CONCH DADDY showed early speed inside a pair of rivals then took control up the backstretch, dueled with outer rival around the bend, lost command at the quarter pole and weakened in the lane. RING GENERAL showed early speed between rivals then chased up the backstretch, dropped around the turn and had little left for the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 93. Maiden Claiming Purse 42000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500, For Each $2,500 To $50,000 1 lb. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ZIO JO bobbled leaving the gate, stalked the pace on the inside, raced in traffic behind the top pair in upper stretch, angled out with a furlong left to run, drew alongside inner rivals and got up while being corrected late. ZIHUATANEJO stepped to the front and showed the way early, challenged on the far turn and lost command past the quarter pole, fought back to regain control in upper stretch but could not hold off the winner late. STORM THE NIGHT stalked in the two path, bid outside the leader at the five-sixteenths pole, took over past the quarter pole, lost command outside the eight pole, fought between rivals late and faltered. CLOONEY traveled in mid-pack on the inside, steadied off heels at the nine-sixteenths pole, saved ground through the far turn and kept on to round out the superfecta. RUSSELLS HUSTLE hit the gate and bobbled at the start, pulled between rivals early, chased two to three wide into the drive and lacked the needed late punch. BLUEGRASS RYDER tracked three deep on both turns, moved out in upper stretch and failed to produce a bid. REIGN OVER ME was off slow to begin, tugged on the inside early, moved out on the backstretch, raced outside a rival into the far turn, came three wide into the stretch, moved out and failed to menace. MOON TIME reserved in the beginning, raced outside a rival in the two path towards the rear, moved inward and saved ground around the far turn and could not make an impact. SWISS GOLD was antsy in the starting gate, broke slow and outward, trailed to the stretch and never got involved.
